    <div class="box">
        <p>
            This paragraph is contained within a 600px by 400px box. The box has a 2px black
            dotted border and a background color of #D1D631. The paragraph itself does not
            extend the box, but it shows how text is displayed within the constraints of a
            box model.
        </p>
        <p>
            The box model is an essential concept in web design that includes the content
            area, padding, border, and margin. Understanding how to manipulate these
            properties is crucial for creating well-structured and visually appealing web
            pages.
